In depth report

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Cheng Wei and Wan Xiaotian contributed reporting from Quanzhou

Yang Jinqiang rented the sheep farm, planted fruit trees first, then opened the battlefield, and finally built a steel-framed building, which survived numerous waves of demolition and demolition violations, and carried out reconstruction, adding at least 3,000 tons of additional load-bearing capacity without significant structural strengthening, into the Grand Hotel.

When new crown pneumonia epidemic situation arrives, here becomes "the Centralism Medicine Observation Point" . Until March 7th, when the building collapsed.

Twenty-nine people, from affected areas or with a history of travel, were found to be negative for nucleic acid but needed to be observed for 14 days before they could start living and working in Quanzhou. But in the end, they didn't make it out.

At around 1100 hours on March 12,112 hours after the accident, rescuers found the body of the last person trapped at the site of the Xinjia hotel collapse. Of the 71 people trapped, 29 died and 42 survived.

On the same day, a source from the Emergency Response Department told the media that the hotel's illegal construction and repeated illegal renovation "exposed loopholes and blind areas that have long caused potential safety risks by the local authorities' failure to implement their work safety supervision responsibilities. ". He also revealed that the State Council has set up the Hotel Xin Jia "37" collapse accident investigation team to carry out the accident investigation.

The owner of the building, Yang Jinqiang, has been taken into custody, Quanzhou reported earlier.

"bought" by Yang Jinqiang

In Shiguitou (place name) , a village on Quanzhou's Jiangnan Street, Yang Jinqiang, 65, is not highly regarded as a person who does not care about the village and rarely helps its people.

"maybe it's because he was bought, " several elderly villagers told depthpaper. In the early years, Yang's adoptive parents, who had no children, bought him from the Wubao village in Quanzhou for an undisclosed sum, yang's adoptive parents later gave birth to two sons, Yang Jinze and Yang Jinhui, and a daughter, Yang Jinfeng.

But Yang's parents have died, and his relatives or authorities could not be reached for comment.

Yang Jinqiang only went to high school. Villagers said the three brothers were not on good terms. Yang's business was relatively large and he made a lot of money. He lived in a big, luxurious villa, but he rarely helped his two brothers and a sister.

Another detail from the villagers is that some people in the village, who have far less assets than Yang Jinqiang, can donate 50,000 yuan, or 3 million yuan, to build a Yangjia ancestral hall, but Yang seems to have little sympathy for Yang and has not donated a penny. Yang Jinqiang's name, also did not appear in the village of a number of road donations on the stone tablet.

In the village, "depth line" reporters repeatedly saw the village road hardening donations tablet, one of about 1.5 meters wide winding path of the road hardening donations tablet, there is a person named Yang Jinze, the amount of donations of 300 yuan. Individual villagers can not confirm that the "Yang Jinze" is Yang Jinze, the younger brother of Yang Jinqiang.

Several elderly villagers of Yang Jinqiang's evaluation is: "He does not take advantage of the villagers, is already very grateful. "

On the east side of the collapsed Xinjia Hotel, a straight line 940 meters away, is Yang Jinqiang's current house in the village. This one-sided, 40-meter-long house is considered the most luxurious and magnificent in the village.

Yang Jinqiang's european-style Villa residence in the village. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

The Double Steel Gate is about 2.5 m wide and 2 m high. The Iron Gate is made of black paint, and the Golden Pattern highlights the noble spirit. However, the door around the red couplet has been torn, leaving only 5 self-adhesive and a part of the red couplet paper.

Enter the gate left 2 meters, step 5 steps, is a platform, straight line 8 meters, that is the building gate. The whole building is a european-style Villa, respectively 2,3,4 floor patchwork, red roof, the roof has lightning Rod.

These characteristics make Yang Jinqiang's house very different from other villagers'houses. Inside, birds CHIRP, but the doors and windows are closed. A few of Yang's neighbors avoided talking about him at all. To the reporter all questions, all said "does not know" .

The collapsed Xinjia Hotel, which was used for raising sheep more than 20 years ago, was later contracted by Yang Jinqiang to grow fruit trees, villagers said. But the fruit trees did not grow long, on the push off the fruit trees, do for a period of time the Sandfield and stacking yard. Here, around 2012, a large building near the completion of 2013, Yang Jinqiang construction of steel structure buildings. In 2018, after renovation, it became the Xinjia hotel.

Yang has three daughters: Yang Guifen, Yang Guihong and Yang Guiyu. In 2006, he and his three daughters invested 3 million yuan to register Quanzhou Xinxing Electrical and Mechanical Industry and Trade Co. , Ltd. (3.03% for each of the three daughters) , located in the Jiangnan Street Shangcun Community (in the old farm) , Licheng district, Quanzhou City, the site of the collapsed Xinjia Hotel.

The registered capital and the paid-in capital have not been announced. The address is the lobby on the ground floor 1, floors 4 to 6 at No. 1688. The "Xinjia hotel in Licheng district" , that is, the collapse of the Xinjia hotel.

The XINJIA hotel was built in 2013 and renovated in 2018, according to an official announcement. On January 22,2019, the public security fire brigade of Licheng district, Quanzhou City issued the "opinions on the review of the fire record of the completion and acceptance of construction projects, " in which the construction unit signed and received a column, it is written in Yang Guihong's handwriting —— A name that is identical to one of Yang's daughters.

Xinjia hotel applied for re-inspection on January 15,2019. After data review and on-site inspection, the project was comprehensively assessed as having passed the fire protection re-inspection upon completion of the project."

Xinhua News Agency reported on March 14 that at the first plenary meeting of the investigation group on the "37" collapse of the Xinjia Hotel, the State Council, according to a preliminary investigation: "The project did not fulfill the capital construction procedures, no planning and construction permits, there are illegal construction, illegal transformation and other serious problems, especially the housing owners found the settlement of the Housing Foundation and load-bearing column deformation and other major accident precursors, still feel lucky, continue to operate illegally and risk-taking; local relevant functional departments are not in place supervision, 'fight non-governance violation' in form, resulting in security checkpoints layer upon layer of invalidation, resulting in a tragic accident. "

Xinjia hotel in the above-mentioned fire inspection, what exactly has been done to rectify and adjust, who participate in the information review and on-site inspection of the fire inspection given qualified, this is to be confirmed by the investigation team of the State Council.

Villagers said that the Xinjia Hotel project under Yang Jinqiang's name may have more problems than that. The land was originally the collective land of the village and used to be a sheep farm. Yang Jinqiang was contracted to plant fruit trees, which were not planted for long, on the bulldozer used to pile up Sandlot, and so on, later built a steel structure of the housing, land procedures doubt.

According to the regulations, how was this construction project, which may not have a Land tenure certificate, built? Land, Housing and construction, fire, industry and commerce, market supervision and other departments, as well as villages, communities, streets and so on can not escape responsibility, because in the process, the procedures of these departments, each other premise, without the previous procedures, can not carry out the next procedures.

Moreover, even after the outbreak, Quanzhou, Licheng district are still strict violations of the building, and sometimes reported. How was Xinjia Hotel selected to be the "Central Medical Observation Point" for the new pneumonia outbreak? Reporters at the local multi-department to interview, but did not respond.

For 20 years, the sheep farm became an observation point. On March 7, the building where the Xinjia hotel was located collapsed.

Three seconds to collapse

Surveillance from a nearby gas station showed that the Xinjia hotel in the video had lights in the room before it collapsed toward the South Ring Road on the night of March 7,19 -- 15 -- 55, but the entire building went dark and without power the moment the third floor hit the ground.

The whole collapse took only three seconds.

After that, the video was filled with dust and floated tens of meters away. The official Weibo account of the local emergency management department announced the time of the collapse as "around 19:05 on March 7. ". Some media statements about the time of the collapse, most of the day "1730 or so. ".

The surveillance video shows that before the collapse, the building did not have the previous media reports "there was a violent shaking back and forth, " not to mention the first backward (north) collapse, and then under the pull of the steel frame, then reverse forward (south) collapse process.

"CONTOUR" reporters found that the building's collapse shape, the basic front (south side) complete collapse, but the building behind (north side)3 to 7 floors are basically intact. Seen from the air with a drone, its shape looks like someone ripped open a box and exposed many squares inside.

This collapse shape, the hotel in 3 to 7 floors, and the back (north) of the residents, was not buried by the collapse of debris, the survival rate is great, and living in the front (south) of the room, the survival rate is low. This is the incident after a few hours, to the morning of March 8, then search and rescue dozens of reasons. Because these people are in "ripped-side boxes" and the openings of these boxes are "upside down" , it is relatively easy to rescue them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Seen from the top, the 3,4,5,6,7 floors behind the original (north side) of Xinjia hotel were not buried because the north side facade disappeared after the collapse. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

But rescue efforts after the morning of March 8th have been particularly difficult. The reason is that the roof is a monolithic cast-in-place reinforced concrete slab, like a 50-meter-long and 20-meter-wide "flat-topped hat" , after the collapse, this "hat" is roughly 8 meters wide and basically paved with the ground, but another 12 meters covered the collapsed building at an angle of 45 to 60 degrees.

Seen from a distance, the hat looks like the entire facade of the building, but there is not even a window. But in fact, the front of the building is all glass curtain wall, in the collapse of the first paved to the ground. This roof "hat" greatly increased the difficulty of rescue.

During the rescue, the reporter from the contour noted that in the previous two days, in order to prevent large-scale machinery from dragging, moving or digging the reinforced concrete "hat" , injuring the trapped people who may still survive below, each rescue team could only be divided into several working areas, using life detectors and search and rescue dogs, as in earthquake rescue, using hydraulic machinery or electric Hammer, carefully cut some rescue holes in the concrete floor slab, and then through shouting, instrument detection, rescue dog detection, etc. , decide whether to continue to cut through the next layer of laminated floors, or to expand the area of the rescue hole to carry out rescue.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The roof, made of cast-in-place concrete on corrugated steel, was the first major obstacle to rescue. People had to manually cut through some of the "skylights" to help. Based on the thickness and area of the concrete, the roof weighs up to 250 tons. By Cheng Wei, isobath reporter, photography

Because of caution, this rescue method is slow to progress, a rescue point or a rescue hole detection, cut hole, further determine the direction and rescue point, determine the rescue plan, rescue personnel enter, how to safely rescue, etc. , are very time-consuming. A 30-person rescue team, in such rescue, eight hours to cut 2 meters square rescue hole, sent deep 2 to 3 floors of reconnaissance, rescue, has been extremely tired.

Several rescue workers who withdrew from the "line of fire" said that in many cases such rescue operations can only be carried out in a less destructive way, and that the cut steel and concrete can only be carried out by the rescue workers standing in a line, piece by piece, bucket by bucket.

By 2100 hours on the night of March 9, the rescue had entered the second stage, using heavy machinery such as excavators to first remove the "hats" , which had been laid on the ground relatively gently, and then manually attaching a rope to the waist, "cover plates" were cut with impact hammers to a size of 2 to 6 metres square and removed one by one. In addition, two excavators were started and a full excavation was carried out on the east side of the collapse site.

This excavation, the use of heavy machinery first combined with the work of the way. That is, while the excavator is cleaning up the scene, a group of Rescue Team members always pay attention to the digging surface and cleaning surface, in time to find the possible trapped or victims.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 20:00 on March 11, the Golden 73-hour rescue has passed, only the last trapped person has not been found, 24 hours of uninterrupted high-intensity rescue finally suspended. At 11 am on the 12th, rescue teams found the body of the last victim. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

On the morning of March 10,120, the reporter of "isodepth line" photographed two excavators working on the easternmost side of the site of the collapse and found the body of a victim. Rescue workers immediately followed, putting the victim's body into a white body bag and passing it from hand to hand on a stretcher, moving to a level open area, the rescue team members formed a circle around the body and observed a moment of silence. Then, four to five people from each side were carried on stretchers to transport the body to the relevant vehicles.

To March 10, the rescue team began to collapse site a row out of six operations, the full use of heavy machinery, synchronous operation, loud, clean up fast.

March 11 at 20:00, the gold rescue 72 hours have passed, the rescue team has been suspended for many days, the heavy machinery shutdown. At 11 a.m. on March 12, rescue teams found the body of the last victim.

The steel structure of the building itself, is the second major obstacle in this rescue, can only be manually cut with a gas welding, and then used to grab the machine loaded into the slag truck away. By Cheng Wei, isobath reporter

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For the rest of the project, heavy machinery was all that was needed to clear away the debris. However, as of 12 to 14 March, when the rescue teams withdrew, the remaining debris was not immediately cleared or removed, but was surrounded by a temporary wall and guarded by guards.

The scourge of steel?

According to information released by the local authorities, the collapsed building was built in 2013 on an area of about five acres, with seven floors, 1,000 square meters per floor and a 22-meter high steel structure. In 2018, it was converted into Xin Jia Hotel and opened in June of that year. The hotel has 66 rooms in total. After the outbreak of NCP, Xinjia hotel was used as an observation point of TCM for people from key epidemic areas or those who had relevant travel history.

The reporter of "isodepth line" asked the local construction management department about the building's construction, renovation and approval procedures and related information, but did not respond.

The satellite map shows that the building is 50 metres long and 20 metres wide in the east-west direction, and that behind the building there is a two-storey building in the shape of a "7" , with a horizontal length of 100 metres above the "7" . The building and "7" between the building, the original 4 meters spacing, after the addition of a 2-story building, "7"-shaped building and the main building of Xinjia hotel connected together.

The street view map and historical street view map show that the back (north side) of the main building of Xin Jia Hotel and the approximately 4-meter wall at the back of the East and West sides are covered with white tiles instead of glass curtain walls, both the East and west side walls and the front (south side) are glass curtain walls.

Historical satellite maps show that in 2012, the foundation (geosphere beam) of the building, the first two blocks on the south-east side, had the largest range, with an east-west span of about 18 metres, respectively, while the foundation intersections of the remaining blocks had spans of about 7 to 8 metres. The historical satellite map also shows that on the west side of the building (directly to the left of the building) , there are four main steel columns from south to north, each about 7 metres away.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Satellite Images show that in 2012, when the building was in its early stages of construction, the first column on the West Side (left) had four pillars, the second column had only three pillars, and the east side (right) had three areas to the south with a foundation span of 15 to 18 metres. Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent, cartography

But the second row of steel columns from west to east, only three. The span between the first and second steel columns is about 15 meters, and the distance between the second and third columns is about 5 meters. Between each column, there is a strong north-south connection to Kaifeng on each floor, and between the first column and the Second Column, there are 11 east-west crossbeams, which are placed between the North and South Kaifeng.

The historical satellite map shows that no other columns have been installed at this time.

While waiting for the rescue site for 4 days, the reporter of "depth contour" focused on the steel structure of the building's columns, the base and foot of the columns, the connection point between the beams and the columns and the structure and connection mode, type and size of connection between each cross beam and Kaifeng. And shot with the person's head, hands, feet and other reference objects can be directly compared with the video, pictures, sent to the domestic steel construction professionals identification.

Deng Weiming, general manager of Chongqing Haomen Tiehua Co. , Ltd. and chairman of Chongqing Steel Zhijia Supply Chain Management Co. , Ltd. , who has 23 years of experience in Steel Structure Construction and has participated in many major steel structure construction projects in Guangzhou and Chongqing, this was evaluated on 12 March.

Deng Weiming, after poring over a variety of contrasting photos and videos of the building's steel structure taken by the reporter of the isohyline over the past few days, said that seven h-shaped steel columns of 350 mm had been erected on the front side of the building, and the spacing between each pillar is about nine meters. "usually we use 350 mm h-beams, which can not be more than six meters across, " he said. "His main beams are more than nine meters apart, and the largest north-south columns are 17 to 18 meters across. This is a rare use, and most people would not dare to use it. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The rescue site was roughly divided into 6 working surfaces, corresponding to the building's Front (south side) of the seven h-section steel columns. Professionals with 23 years of experience in steel construction say few in the industry would dare to use such a non triangular structure, typically 350 mm H-beam, with a span of no more than 6M, but the Xinjia Hotel's span, between 10,000 feet and 18 feet. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

Other domestic media obtained from the interviewees photos show that the building's 1-floor car sales hall, Hollow north-south Span, in about 18 meters.

Usually steel structures are triangular in shape because they are the most stable, such as the Jialing River Bridge in Chongqing, Wushan Yangtze River Bridge and some super tall buildings, he said. The basic structural form of steel structure, are based on triangle structure, but the basic building structure of Xinjia hotel is quadrangle, once the force, it will be very unstable.

In addition, Deng Weiming also believed that h-beam generally can not be used in large-span, high-load-bearing buildings, in particular the need for a large number of load-bearing construction of the load-bearing columns and beams, can only use round seamless steel columns, it also requires inpouring concrete to increase its strength, since h-beams are subject to certain forces in the forward direction, but are vulnerable to forces in the lateral and slightly twisted directions.

Even if there is no new multi-storey hotel in the building, he said, this kind of design and construction is not something that someone with design experience or building experience would dare to do.

The roof concrete area of Xinjia hotel is 1,000 square meters, which is cast in situ on a layer of corrugated steel plate. The average thickness of the concrete is about 10 cm, and the volume is 100 cubic meters, the density of ordinary concrete is 2.5 tons per cubic meter, and the weight of the roof concrete of the building can be calculated to be 250 tons.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Base of 7 main h-section steel columns on the Front (south) side of Xinjia hotel. At the bottom of the column is a simple triangular steel support. The support structure, which is not pictured in the early days of the steel structure, is suspected to have been added during the hotel's renovation, but the triangular base, which is less than half a metre deep, is a drop in the bucket for the extra load. The left side of the figure shows the excavator track for comparison. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

In addition, as a result of the renovation of the hotel on the 3rd to 6th floors of the building, the floors are also cast-in-place reinforced concrete, adding a total of 4 floors of the 3rd, 4th, 5th and 6th floors, the thickness of each floor in a conventional building is 8 to 12 centimetres, with a median thickness of 10 centimetres, and the additional four floors added by the conversion of the hotel alone weigh 1,000 tons.

Aerial photos show that the hotel's seventh floor is only about 2.5 meters high, but the floor of the seventh floor, which is still cast-in-place reinforced concrete, adds another 250 tons of weight to the building.

In addition, the reporter of the "depth contour" also confirmed from the rescue workers on the spot, as well as several times during the four-day on-site observation, that the modified hotel room partition wall inside the building is made of cement and red brick, the hotel has about 18 rooms on each floor (18 rooms are shown in aerial photos, the official number of rooms is 66, not including linen rooms and working rooms) . At least 19 partitions are needed on each floor, the length of the partition wall is 18 metres and the height of the partition wall is 3 metres, excluding the partition wall of the corridor which is 2 metres wide. The width of each red brick is 11.5 cm, and the two sides of each brick are calculated to be covered with cement paste of 1 cm. Based on this calculation, about 692.55 cubic metres of red bricks (without calculating the cement between the bricks) are calculated according to 13.5 cm. The density of each cubic metre of red brick is 1.8 tons, these partition walls weigh 1,247 tons.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A series of field photographs show that the floors of the hotel are made of reinforced concrete and the partition walls are made of red brick and cement. A simple calculation shows that the hotel built in the 3rd to 7th floors of the building will add more than 3,000 tons of weight. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

This calculation does not take into account the four retaining walls on the north and south sides of the four-storey building.

This means that even excluding the hotel's bathrooms, other renovations, furniture, appliances, water and electricity networks, the first round of the renovation of the hotel will add more than 3,000 tons of weight.

Previous estimates by some media outlets suggested the hotel would add around 300 tonnes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The steel structure problems of Xinjia hotel are, first, the use of h-section steel with extremely poor side force and torsion resistance, second, the use of non-stable triangular structure, third, the connection between the steel structure, only the use of drilling and screw connection, instead of using triangular angle bars or reinforcements, huge loads were placed inside, leading to collapse. By Cheng Wei, isobath correspondent

Deng Weiming said that the collapse of the building, which normally uses h-beams of up to three storeys, actually used h-beams to build seven storeys and built a hotel, because all the walls in the built-in hotel were built on steel structures, so virtually all the walls are not involved in the load-bearing below 3 stories, are load-bearing, this practice is very rare.

Two refits

At 18:00 p.m. on March 11, the Leading Group of emergency rescue work in Quanzhou, Fujian Province, held a press conference on the rescue and disposal of the building collapse incident at the Xinjia hotel in Licheng district, announcing the preliminary investigation of the accident. According to the preliminary investigation, Xinjia hotel in the construction, renovation, approval and other aspects of serious problems.

Speaking at the press conference, Hong Ziqiang, a member of the Standing Committee of the Quanzhou Municipal Committee and Executive Vice Mayor, said that after preliminary investigations, Xinjia hotel did have serious problems in terms of construction, renovation and approval.

However, the local release of this information "thrown" to the higher investigation team.

"We have consolidated the relevant evidence, taken compulsory measures according to law against those responsible, and also taken necessary measures to preserve property, " Hong said. "We will submit all the preliminary investigations to the investigation team at a higher level. "

He said that in the course of the investigation, every aspect of hotel construction, renovation, operation and supervision, as well as being recommended as a centralized quarantine health observation point, will not be missed, the units and individuals involved in violation of laws and regulations, dereliction of duty and dereliction of duty, including public officials, will not be tolerated or let off.

But the powers to investigate and deal with the accident quickly fell out of Quanzhou's hierarchy and were handed over to the State Department's Accident Investigation team.

March 12th, pei Wentian, director of the Safety Foundation Department of the Ministry of Emergency Management, responded to the media, saying: "The preliminary investigation shows that this is a production safety responsibility accident. ". This hotel's illegal construction and repeated illegal reconstruction have exposed loopholes and blind areas that have long caused potential safety risks due to the non-implementation of the work safety supervision responsibilities of the local authorities."

Pei Wentian said that in accordance with the relevant provisions of the Regulations on Production Safety Accident Reporting and investigation and handling, the State Council decided to set up an investigation team to investigate the "37" collapse of the Xinjia hotel in Quanzhou, Fujian Province, and to launch an investigation into the accident to quickly find out the cause, those responsible for the accident shall be investigated for their relevant responsibilities, including legal liabilities, in strict accordance with laws and regulations.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 2300 hours on the night of March 10, five workers wearing blue helmets entered the rescue site and used steel tape and Vernier calipers to measure the basic parameters of the seven h-shaped steel columns on the front side of the hotel. Professionals with years of experience in steel construction say the steel frame is 350 mm in size. Other media had previously described the steel structure as 600mm, which is out of proportion to the figure's hand. By Cheng Wei, isobath reporter, photography

A structural engineer from a famous design institute in Chongqing, who did not want to be named, said on March 11 that, the uniform load (including dead weight, partition wall, furniture and so on) of reinforced concrete frame structure is about 1.1 ton to 1.4 ton per square meter. The uniform load of steel structure is smaller than that of reinforced concrete frame structure.

He stressed that the weight of the load, can not be used as a basis for judging collapse, because in the design of building structures, even if the weight is large, as long as it is designed and built according to the design and construction specifications, the buildings that were built were safe from collapse.

According to media reports, a manager surnamed Lin said the building had recently been built on the other side of the hotel. The structural engineer said on March 11 that if the design, construction, materials and modification is in compliance, the "repair foundation" behavior, may be the cause of the collapse of the building.

As of March 12, the Department of Emergency Management Security Infrastructure Division and Quanzhou Emergency Rescue Leading Group have confirmed the "illegal construction of this hotel, many illegal reconstruction" this fact.

Information from local villagers said that before the collapse, the renovation of the ground floor, "knocked down the load-bearing wall, " became the cause of the collapse of the building. Due to the time and can not contact the second renovation of the hotel units, responsible persons, workers, can not get the second renovation of the hotel, renovation, and the collapse of the building.

According to a local construction worker involved in the rescue, steel structures usually do not take into account the problem of bearing walls, which were later added with so many layers of hotels and added so much weight, there will certainly be new load-bearing consideration and structural reinforcement, otherwise no one dare to build a few floors in the steel frame. But, after the building is decorated, the person that decorate behind does not necessarily know that is the bearing wall that can not move, the boss says knock off the space to hit a bit bigger, knock on. But he immediately said that this is only his personal speculation, not empirical support.

As soon as the personage inside course of study sees this picture, blurt out: "This is a common factory building structure, can not bear huge amount of load! Several villagers said that the collective land was not sold to Yang Jinqiang, how it was sold, how much money sold, the village has never announced. Some villagers pointed out that Yang Jinqiang paid off the relevant officials in the village and the city where he lived, eventually allowing the construction of this problematic project and obtaining construction, fire fighting, industry and commerce, and the possible land use certificate, title card and a series of procedures.

However, the information from the villagers has not yet been confirmed by the local village committee and relevant departments.

On the afternoon of March 14, several police officers were searching for evidence in Yang's luxurious villa and refused to allow journalists to stay in the building. Yang Jinqiang, the village secretary, and Chen Zhiyong, the village director, were at the rescue headquarters opposite the site of the collapse, a member of Yang's community (the village committee) said on the afternoon of March 14.

But the two people are not here, so can not confirm the accident site, such as land procedures.
